The paper deals with the problem of discovering association rules in relational data, which is a core topic in database systems (cs.DB). The proposed approach involves generating and evaluating patterns, which is a common theme in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges of pruning operators, which is a common problem in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The discovery of association rules is also related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves finding patterns and relationships in data.
